                                        <div class="content" data-aos="fade-right">
                                            <p>According to Canadian Law, all provinces and territories provide universal, publicly funded health care to all citizens and legal residents of Canada. In other words, most basic health services are available to the patient at no cost.  Certain procedures that are not considered necessary (such as cosmetic surgery and a number of dental care procedures) are generally not covered, but the list of free services differ from province to province. New Brunswick Medicare covers most medically required services, which is provided by medical practitioners. In addition to Medicare, health insurance can be purchased from major private sector insurers.

                                            </p>
